1
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:15,500
I can't let you have that,
Madame.

2
00:00:15,567 --> 00:00:17,833
Because you gave us
counterfeit money.

3
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:19,700
You must have switched my money.

4
00:00:19,767 --> 00:00:21,000
This hat is mine.

5
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:23,600
I'm still being respectful
because you are a store patron.

6
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:26,933
But from now on, you will
be banned from this store.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,067
What the heck is that?

8
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:29,000
That's fake!

9
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:31,767
I couldn't check all of it.

10
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:34,000
You're so stupid!
You didn't check it!

11
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:36,400
Look at what happened!

12
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:37,800
I spent a lot of money,

13
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:41,133
but it's worth seeing Rina get
dragged out of that boutique.

14
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,967
She's like a slave.

15
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:45,633
She was so embarrassed.

16
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:50,000
You shouldn't prolong
your misunderstanding.

17
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:51,933
You love him, right?

18
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:57,933
You might lose him just
like how we lost your mom.

19
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,333
I've come to terms that Yenyen
is the one you love.

20
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:05,867
I've always been there for her,
but I'm hurting too.

21
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:07,100
Who's there for me?

22
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:10,467
Please, don't be mad at Red.

23
00:01:10,533 --> 00:01:12,633
He's been going through
a lot right now.

24
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:15,533
He even told me that
you're pushing him away.

25
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:17,333
Oh, please, Sabina.

26
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:20,067
Don't act as if you care
about our relationship.

27
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:23,067
You're together for the baby,
right?

28
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:24,500
And now that the baby's gone,

29
00:01:24,567 --> 00:01:29,000
maybe it's time for you guys
to rethink your relationship.

30
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:30,233
You two are not happy anymore.

31
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:33,167
Mrs. Madrigal might be
in an important business.

32
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:34,267
I don't want to interrupt.

33
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:36,833
I won't let this opportunity go.

34
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,733
I just want to, you know,
meet her.

35
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,333
Say hello, and introduce myself.

36
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,667
Right?

37
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:43,000
Mrs. Madrigal?

38
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:44,100
Mrs. Madrigal.

39
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,367
Mrs. Madrigal, hello!

40
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:49,233
This is Rina Ramos.

41
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:53,833
Mrs. Madrigal, you know,

42
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:57,200
I have a feeling we can
really be good friends.

43
00:01:57,267 --> 00:01:59,233
Our husbands are
business partners.

44
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,733
They have a business together.

45
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:04,533
Mrs. Madrigal,
can you open the curtains?

46
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,600
I don't bite.

47
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:09,167
Yes, I just want to meet you.

48
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:10,233
Mrs. Madrigal?

49
00:02:11,767 --> 00:02:12,733
Mrs. Madrigal?

50
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,967
Ma'am, excuse me.

51
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:15,133
Yes?

52
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:17,867
Mrs. Madrigal wants me
to tell you

53
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:21,267
that this is not the right time
to socialize with you.

54
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:23,700
And please respect her privacy.

55
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:24,567
I'm sorry.

56
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,300
Did she say that?
Yes, Ma'am.

57
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:30,400
Not the right time?

58
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:37,033
Eden...

59
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,267
I'm glad it's just
you and me here.

60
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,467
Your in-laws aren't here.

61
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:43,067
I don't feel comfortable coming
here when they're home.

62
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:45,700
They're not my in-laws yet.
We're still not married.

63
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:47,333
Eden.

64
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,833
But, I think it's
better that way.

65
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,833
Aunt Rina might be right.

66
00:02:55,433 --> 00:02:58,333
Perhaps, I don't know
Red that well yet.

67
00:02:59,333 --> 00:02:59,700
Hey.

68
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:03,067
We rushed into things.

69
00:03:03,133 --> 00:03:04,833
Remember, he's supposed
to go to the States.

70
00:03:07,067 --> 00:03:09,133
And I stopped him from leaving
because I was pregnant.

71
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:12,200
Eden, what are you saying?

72
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:15,700
I know you two are in love.

73
00:03:16,433 --> 00:03:18,500
That's not fair to your baby.

74
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:21,767
You had the baby because
you two love each other.

75
00:03:21,867 --> 00:03:24,133
Red is sincere about
how he feels about you.

76
00:03:24,933 --> 00:03:29,467
I can't imagine what you're
going through right now.

77
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:33,133
But don't doubt the love
you have for each other.

78
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:37,000
I know that Red loves you.

79
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:39,700
What you have for
each other is real.

80
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:43,633
Would you fight for it
if it wasn't real?

81
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,867
Look at what happened
after I did that.

82
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:49,400
My own mother cursed me.

83
00:03:50,067 --> 00:03:51,233
I lost my mom.

84
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,033
And I lost my baby.

85
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:57,167
And now I'm afraid I'm going
to lose Red too.

86
00:03:59,533 --> 00:04:02,000
That's why...

87
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,500
you can't let that happen, okay?

88
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,400
The nerve.

89
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:23,167
So, did you get to meet her?

90
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,167
No!

91
00:04:24,233 --> 00:04:25,933
And you know what?
I don't want to meet her.

92
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,767
I don't care about her anymore.

93
00:04:27,867 --> 00:04:29,867
She thinks she's
all that important.

94
00:04:29,933 --> 00:04:31,067
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

95
00:04:31,133 --> 00:04:33,667
She said the two of you
were best friends.

96
00:04:33,733 --> 00:04:35,933
That's what she wanted.

97
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:36,900
Oh, boy.

98
00:04:38,167 --> 00:04:41,000
Don't be scared.
I'm not mad at you.

99
00:04:41,067 --> 00:04:42,700
- That woman is a liar.
- Yes, Ma'am.

100
00:04:42,767 --> 00:04:44,100
She's just pulling your leg.

101
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:49,033
All right, I'll let this slide,
okay?

102
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:52,333
But you have to do
something for me.

103
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:53,967
Okay, Ma'am.

104
00:04:57,367 --> 00:04:59,933
She said this was not
the time to meet her.

105
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,500
She said if I wanted
to be friends with her,

106
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,233
this is not the right way.

107
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:07,733
Hold on, is there a protocol?
What is she?

108
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:08,667
A queen?

109
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,400
I told you so.

110
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:23,733
My God!

111
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,300
Rina, please.

112
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,867
Can you just let it go?

113
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:31,233
Aren't we here to relax?

114
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,533
Let's forget about
Mrs. Madrigal.

115
00:05:35,667 --> 00:05:36,867
Okay, all right.

116
00:05:36,933 --> 00:05:38,933
If you want, we can just leave.

117
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,967
- Let's go home.
- No, no.

118
00:05:41,033 --> 00:05:43,933
This is our time.
This is our date.

119
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,867
Have you ordered?

120
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,500
I don't know.

121
00:05:47,567 --> 00:05:49,133
I was wondering if you want
to choose something else.

122
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,200
I was trying to order
something here,

123
00:05:52,267 --> 00:05:54,667
but let's see what we can get.

124
00:05:54,733 --> 00:05:56,367
They were pretty good.

125
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:58,100
I think it's pretty good.

126
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,200
Ma'am, Sir. Here's your order.

127
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:02,567
Oh, wow!

128
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:03,933
That looks special.

129
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,167
Is that what we ordered?

130
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:08,167
May I?

131
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,200
What the?

132
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:12,233
Oh my God!

133
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,700
What is that?

134
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:16,967
I'm sorry.

135
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:18,067
What is that?

136
00:06:19,533 --> 00:06:21,567
Who told you to serve that?

137
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,367
What the hell is that?
Is that a joke?

138
00:06:25,433 --> 00:06:26,333
What is this?

139
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,267
What kind of service is this?

140
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:30,500
Who told you to serve this?

141
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,033
Who told you to do this?

142
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:36,067
Are you hungry?

143
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:37,367
Here you go. Eat this!

144
00:06:38,533 --> 00:06:39,167
Eat!

145
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:44,100
Surprise, surprise, Amanda.

146
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:44,800
Have some more.

147
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:49,967
What do you want from me?
Why did you bring me here?

148
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:55,900
I just want to see you for the
last time looking like this.

149
00:06:55,967 --> 00:07:01,667
So gross, pitiful,
and no one to turn to.

150
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:05,333
- I'm sorry, Ma'am.
- Who told you to do this?

151
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,233
We didn't know what was inside.
It was covered.

152
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:10,167
Don't lie to me.

153
00:07:10,233 --> 00:07:11,767
You can't tell me you
don't know anything.

154
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,067
Who told you to do this?

155
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:14,400
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

156
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:17,067
I'll have this restaurant
shut down!

157
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:17,800
You monsters!

158
00:07:19,733 --> 00:07:21,167
What is this? Scraps?

159
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:27,367
Do something about this.

160
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:30,867
Get their names.

161
00:07:30,933 --> 00:07:31,800
Get this out of here.
- Get it off the table.
- Hello?

162
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:33,700
Hello?
Hello?

163
00:07:35,867 --> 00:07:36,767
Hello?

164
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:39,833
Did you like my lunch treat,
Rina?

165
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:41,733
Hello?

166
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:43,600
Who is this?

167
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:49,033
You deserve the food I sent you.

168
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,833
Who are you? Hey!

169
00:07:52,900 --> 00:08:02,700
That's the kind of food
that pigs like you eat.

170
00:08:02,767 --> 00:08:05,667
It's gross and spoiled.

171
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:08,433
You beast! Show yourself!

172
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,567
You coward! Who are you?

173
00:08:10,633 --> 00:08:11,500
Who are you?

174
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:14,567
Hon, who is it?

175
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:17,200
Some idiot!

176
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:19,800
Okay, try to calm down.

177
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:20,433
Calm down.

178
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:24,600
Who's doing this to us, Victor?
Who is it?

179
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:28,833
Ma'am, Sir, I'm sorry
about what happened.

180
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:31,100
Are you trying to apologize?

181
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:34,000
We don't know anything
about that food.

182
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:36,700
We don't know who did that.

183
00:08:36,767 --> 00:08:38,667
Let's get out of here!
You better prepare yourself.

184
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:39,467
Come on, Hon.

185
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:41,100
I will have this
place shut down!

186
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:42,133
I will get you for this!

187
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,300
- Ma'am, please don't.
- Come on, let's go.

188
00:08:43,367 --> 00:08:44,000
- Come on, Hon. That's enough.
- Ma'am, I'm sorry.
I don't want to stay here.

189
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:46,233
Get out of my way!

190
00:09:02,267 --> 00:09:05,733
Didn't you have a fight with
anyone who could do this to us?

191
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:08,533
No.

192
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,667
You know me,
I get along with everyone.

193
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:15,033
And besides, if that person
has a grudge against me,

194
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:16,333
why did she call you and not me?

195
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:22,533
Rina, you could be her target
because of our business...

196
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:24,800
Business?

197
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:26,233
What business?

198
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:27,400
You didn't tell me
anything about that.

199
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:32,467
Here you go.

200
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:34,167
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

201
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:35,500
I'm worried that they
will file a complaint.

202
00:09:35,567 --> 00:09:37,100
We might lose our job.

203
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:38,400
Don't believe her.

204
00:09:38,467 --> 00:09:40,333
I got you.

205
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:44,700
The wife of the restaurant's
owner is my best friend.

206
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:47,233
You won't lose your job.

207
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:47,800
Okay?

208
00:09:48,367 --> 00:09:49,067
Okay.

209
00:09:49,133 --> 00:09:50,133
Thank you.

210
00:09:54,267 --> 00:09:56,000
No, Victor.

211
00:09:56,067 --> 00:10:01,000
I have a friend that offered
some flimsy business.

212
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,433
I didn't accept it.

213
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,800
I didn't make a deal with her.

214
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:05,833
I don't think she's capable
of doing this to me.

215
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:13,167
Well, only one person
who hates us can do this.

216
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:16,833
Someone who's been sending
us all sorts of things.

217
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:19,933
It's Amanda.

218
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,200
You know, you're right, Red.

219
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:31,833
That shameless woman!

220
00:10:33,067 --> 00:10:34,667
She probably did this!

221
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:37,733
Amanda is such a pest!

222
00:10:58,967 --> 00:10:59,400
Red?

223
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,700
Can we talk?

224
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:03,500
Is your mom calling you lately?

225
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:07,300
No, why? Did something happen?

226
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,800
Do you know where she is?

227
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:10,633
No.

228
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,633
Didn't we look for her together?

229
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,267
What happened?

230
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:16,667
I want to see her!

231
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:20,767
I want to tell her to leave
my family alone!

232
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:23,000
Why? What happened?

233
00:11:23,067 --> 00:11:24,700
Someone threatened my mom.

234
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:28,033
Only your mom is capable of
doing something like this.

235
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,167
Yen, I tried to respect
your mom.

236
00:11:34,133 --> 00:11:35,400
But if she won't
stop doing this,

237
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:36,467
I'll forget she's your mom.

238
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:37,867
I might end up hurting her.

239
00:11:37,933 --> 00:11:41,567
Red, don't talk like that.
You're not that kind of person.

240
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:43,967
But she's pushing me
to be like this!

241
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:48,500
Yen, we lost our baby
because of her.

242
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:51,100
And now she's targeting my mom.

243
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:53,300
When is she going to stop?

244
00:12:08,967 --> 00:12:12,867
I've already talked to the event
organizer that you requested.

245
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,767
And they know your taste.

246
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:20,967
Expensive and elegant.

247
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:22,167
That's what you taught me.

248
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:24,700
And you're a fast learner.

249
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,967
Are you ready for this?

250
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:34,033
This world is too small
for Rina and me.

251
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:39,067
Our paths have crossed
many times.

252
00:12:40,033 --> 00:12:42,100
I might not be able to get away
from her next time.

253
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,333
That's not what we planned.

254
00:12:46,167 --> 00:12:50,967
I will choose the day
and time to face her.

255
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:54,633
She better be prepared.

256
00:12:56,433 --> 00:13:00,633
She will finally find out
who Mrs. Madrigal is.

257
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:19,633
I have no idea who could
threaten you like this.

258
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:24,200
It could be Elmer,
but I heard he'd left the town.

259
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:27,033
He left right after he
cheated us of our money.

260
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:34,467
The waiter from that restaurant
is gone.

261
00:13:34,533 --> 00:13:35,967
They said he was assigned
to another branch.

262
00:13:38,433 --> 00:13:39,733
Then follow him!

263
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:44,600
Rina, instead of
focusing on them,

264
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:46,467
why don't you try to think about
who can do this to you?

265
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,267
Red could be right.

266
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:53,700
What if Amanda's
behind all this?

267
00:13:59,467 --> 00:14:00,467
What the?

268
00:14:00,533 --> 00:14:01,567
Oh my God!

269
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:04,033
What is that?

270
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:07,233
Are you hungry?

271
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:08,467
Here. Eat this!

272
00:14:09,767 --> 00:14:10,867
Eat! Go on!

273
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:12,567
Eat!

274
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:14,600
Gross...

275
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:17,733
you're so pitiful.

276
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,467
No one is on your side.

277
00:14:20,267 --> 00:14:21,200
You monster!

278
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:22,867
What a pitiful person.

279
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:24,233
You're a monster!

280
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,433
- You're calling me a monster?
- Yes! Untie me! I will get you!

281
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,467
Amanda can't be behind all this.

282
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:36,333
Isn't she a homeless person now?

283
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,467
For all you know,

284
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:40,033
she might be in a mental
facility by now.

285
00:14:41,067 --> 00:14:42,733
Or perhaps, she's already dead.

286
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,733
I hope she's dead.

287
00:14:46,467 --> 00:14:52,733
It takes someone with a great
resource to do this to me.

288
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,367
And it can't be Amanda.

289
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:07,767
What's that?

290
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,667
Did Victor do you wrong?

291
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:11,600
No.

292
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:13,200
This is not from him.

293
00:15:14,967 --> 00:15:15,500
Thank you.

294
00:15:17,933 --> 00:15:19,533
Wow, party.

295
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,233
Are you going?

296
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:22,000
You are cordially invited

297
00:15:22,067 --> 00:15:28,033
to the home of Mr. and Mrs.
Lucho Madrigal.

298
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:32,033
Housewarming.

299
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,633
I thought you were going
to ignore Mrs. Madrigal.

300
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,200
On this occasion...

301
00:15:39,267 --> 00:15:40,167
maybe not.

302
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:43,567
Since she invited me...

303
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,967
I might come after all.

304
00:15:56,267 --> 00:15:58,433
Are you sure you don't want
to come with us, Eden?

305
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:02,633
I'm not ready to go
to a party yet.

306
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:05,867
Should I just stay home too?

307
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:07,600
Nonsense.

308
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:09,333
Come on, we need to be there.

309
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:13,800
We need to support your dad in
front of his business partners.

310
00:16:13,867 --> 00:16:15,167
That's very important.

311
00:16:16,167 --> 00:16:19,567
And besides, if Eden is not
ready to socialize yet,

312
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:22,433
we shouldn't force her.

313
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:23,400
Right, Eden?

314
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:28,533
Will you be okay?

315
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:32,300
Let's go.

316
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:09,300
I'm staying away from Red
because I'm still hurting.

317
00:17:09,367 --> 00:17:12,600
And I feel like Red is
fine losing the baby.

318
00:17:12,667 --> 00:17:14,100
I can't bear it.

319
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:23,200
I understand where
you're coming from.

320
00:17:23,267 --> 00:17:26,900
But you should
support each other.

321
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:32,300
Because you both lost a child.

322
00:17:33,567 --> 00:17:36,067
You should help each other out.

323
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,333
But...

324
00:17:46,867 --> 00:17:48,167
if you did something wrong,

325
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:52,067
you should apologize.

326
00:17:53,867 --> 00:17:58,933
You shouldn't prolong
your misunderstanding.

327
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,467
You love him, right?

328
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:04,567
You might end up losing him...

329
00:18:05,967 --> 00:18:08,933
just like how we lost your mom.

330
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:18,833
I can't bear it anymore, Auntie.

331
00:18:58,267 --> 00:19:01,400
I never thought they were this
rich to afford this setup.

332
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:05,200
We can be this rich too.

333
00:19:05,267 --> 00:19:08,400
Just handle your business deal
with Mr. Madrigal nicely.

334
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:16,600
Auntie!

335
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:18,933
Hey!

336
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,233
- Hi.
- Hey, Sab.

337
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:22,000
Oh my God, you're here too.

338
00:19:23,767 --> 00:19:24,733
- Uncle.
- Hello.

339
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:26,433
Hi, Red.
Hi.

340
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,533
Come on. Come sit with us.

341
00:19:29,633 --> 00:19:30,700
- Let's go.
- Okay, come on.

342
00:19:30,767 --> 00:19:31,467
Okay.

343
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:38,133
So you're acquainted with
the Madrigals, too, Sab?

344
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:40,433
Yes, Mr. Madrigal
is my dad's friend.

345
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,633
And my mom told me

346
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:44,867
that Mrs. Madrigal
has a very iconic taste.

347
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:47,500
I'm so excited to meet her.

348
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:49,967
Why would you look for someone
else when I'm here?

349
00:19:50,033 --> 00:19:54,133
We're very much alike.
I am as sophisticated as she is.

350
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,167
I'm sure, Auntie.

351
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,033
Red, come sit.

352
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:59,000
Excuse me, guys.

353
00:19:59,067 --> 00:20:00,133
I'm just going to get
some fresh air.

354
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:09,233
Excuse me, Auntie.

355
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:09,800
All right.
- Okay.
- Sure.

356
00:20:12,633 --> 00:20:13,367
Look at that.

357
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:17,267
- It's so nice, right?
- Yes.

358
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:32,500
Good evening, everyone.

359
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,533
Thank you for coming.

360
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,600
We're having a party

361
00:20:38,667 --> 00:20:43,333
to celebrate coming back
to this place.

362
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,267
Now I know...

363
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:51,800
that a lot of you
want to meet my wife.

364
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:53,567
So without further ado,

365
00:20:55,200 --> 00:21:00,100
ladies and gentlemen,
my beautiful wife...

366
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:01,933
Mrs. Madrigal.

367
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:48,233
My wife wants to thank
all of you.

368
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:56,533
She's a little shy,
so she wants to say thank you.

369
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:58,267
She's not used to this
kind of gatherings yet.

370
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:00,033
Thank you so much.

371
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,567
Mrs. Madrigal...

372
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:25,400
that hat is just divine.

373
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:27,867
We are so alike.

374
00:22:27,933 --> 00:22:30,233
We've got so much in common.

375
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:33,800
I wanted that hat too
when I saw it in the shop.

376
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:35,200
See that, I told you.

377
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,367
We could really be good friends.

378
00:23:24,533 --> 00:23:27,400
It's just so hard to believe,
Eden.

379
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:29,467
It's as if your mom
turned into a terrorist.

380
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:31,367
She loves you so much.

381
00:23:31,433 --> 00:23:33,267
Yes, she loves me.

382
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:38,200
If you can love someone so much,

383
00:23:38,267 --> 00:23:41,200
that's how much
you can hate her too.

384
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:43,300
So are you saying that
you hate her too?

385
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:47,167
Yenyen and I used to
be so happy together.

386
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:52,433
But now, all we do is fight.

387
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:56,567
I feel like we're
drifting apart.

388
00:23:56,667 --> 00:23:58,633
Do you know Red Ramos?

389
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:00,367
Rina Ramos' son.

390
00:24:00,433 --> 00:24:02,833
Yes, are you her
son's girlfriend?

391
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,867
Where's Cecile?
I haven't seen her yet.

392
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:05,867
She's right over there.

393
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:07,900
You know what?

394
00:24:07,967 --> 00:24:09,600
Why don't we listen to music?

395
00:24:09,667 --> 00:24:11,100
Oh, this is your favorite!
